text: Calauan, officially the Municipality of Calauan (), is a 2nd class municipality in the province of Laguna, Philippines. The municipality has a land area of 25.25 square miles which constitutes 3.41% of Laguna's total area. According to the 2020 census, 87,693 people lived there.
